!! Engine adapter pattern

tw-graph discovers engines via `$tw.modules.createClassesFromModules("graphengine")`. The adapter exports:

|!Export |!Purpose |
|`name` |Engine identifier (`"Cytoscape"`) |
|`properties` |Aggregated property schema from all `cytoscape-property` modules |
|`init(element, objects, options)` |Create Cytoscape instance, wire events, apply styles |
|`update(objects)` |Delta updates — add/update/remove nodes and edges |
|`destroy()` |Tear down Cytoscape instance and clean up timers |
|`processObjects(changes)` |Delegate to property handlers before engine update |

!! Property handler modules

Each `module-type: cytoscape-property` module declares properties and lifecycle hooks:

|!Module |!Responsibility |
|`id.js` |Assign IDs to nodes/edges |
|`defaults.js` |Apply initial defaults on first init |
|`events.js` |Map Cytoscape events to tw-graph callbacks, blur debouncing, cluster drag detection |
|`position.js` |Track node positions (x/y) for persistence |
|`nodes.js` |Node visual properties: label, size, shape, cluster |
|`edges.js` |Edge visual properties: arrows, stroke, width, label |
|`color.js` |Color mapping with luminance-based font contrast |
|`layout.js` |Hierarchical layout via breadthfirst |
|`physics.js` |COSE layout mapped from vis-network physics parameters |
|`interaction.js` |Zoom, pan, navigation controls |
|`cluster.js` |Interactive cluster management: config persistence, create/rename/delete/assign |

!! Styling strategy

vis-network uses imperative options per node/edge. Cytoscape uses a declarative stylesheet.

The adapter uses a hybrid approach:

* ''Base stylesheet'' — built from graph-level defaults in `buildStylesheet()`, applied via `cy.style().fromJson()`. Uses `[label]` selectors to avoid warnings on elements without label data.
* ''Per-element overrides'' — applied via `ele.style({...})` after data updates, reading from `data._color`, `data._size`, etc.

!! Cluster system

Clusters are managed entirely in JavaScript — no wikitext involvement beyond the `clusterData` graph property.

!!! Data flow

# `cluster.process()` reads the JSON config tiddler during `processObjects()`
# Virtual cluster nodes are injected into `changes.nodes` with `__cluster__` prefix
# `cluster.postApply()` styles them as dashed containers after every init/update
# `events.js` detects drop-on-node via bounding box overlap in `findDropTarget()`
# `cluster.assignCluster()` updates Cytoscape state immediately + persists to config tiddler via `$tw.wiki.addTiddler()`

!!! Ejection detection

* On `grab`: store the node's position in Cytoscape scratch data
* On `drag`: compute distance from grab position, update cluster border color (orange→red gradient)
* On `free`: if distance > 200px and no drop target found → eject from cluster
* On `free`: reset cluster border style via `postApply()`

!!! Module method calling convention

Property handler methods are called with `this` bound to the engine adapter instance (via `forEachProperty`). Inter-method calls within a module must use `exports.methodName.call(this, ...)` to both find the method (on module exports) and preserve the adapter context.

!! Blur debouncing

vis-network fires `blurNode` based on canvas-internal hit testing — moving the mouse from a node to a DOM popup overlay doesn't trigger blur. Cytoscape fires `mouseout` immediately when the pointer leaves the node area.

The events handler debounces blur by 200ms and monitors `.graph-popup` elements via DOM event delegation. If the mouse enters a popup within the delay, the blur is cancelled.

!! Drop target detection

`findDropTarget()` separates cluster containers from regular nodes:

# Cluster containers are preferred — if the drop position is inside any cluster's bounding box, pick the smallest (most nested) cluster
# Regular nodes are fallback — for auto-creating new clusters when dropping node on node
# Excluded: self, descendants, current parent (prevents false re-assignment)

